" data-label=\"Preview\">\n                    <a href=\"https:\/\/www.amazon.com\/dp\/B07YVKL6DQ?tag=700r4hq-20&linkCode=ogi&th=1&psc=1&keywords=magnetic%20oil%20drain%20plug\" title=\"Votex - M12 X 1.25MM Stainless Steel Magnetic Oil Drain Plug with Neodymium Magnet - Made In USA -...\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\" target=\"_blank\">\n                        <img class=\"aawp-product__img\" src=\"https:\/\/m.media-amazon.com\/images\/I\/31DQSRi5aOL.jpg\" alt=\"Votex - M12 X 1.25MM Stainless Steel Magnetic Oil Drain Plug with Neodymium Magnet - Made In USA -...\"  \/>\n                    <\/a>\n                <\/td>\n                <td class=\"aawp-table__td-title\" data-label=\"Product\">\n                    <a class=\"aawp-product__title\" href=\"https:\/\/www.amazon.com\/dp\/B07YVKL6DQ?tag=700r4hq-20&linkCode=ogi&th=1&psc=1&keywords=magnetic%20oil%20drain%20plug\" title=\"Votex - M12 X 1.25MM Stainless Steel Magnetic Oil Drain Plug with Neodymium Magnet - Made In USA -...\"\n                       rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\" target=\"_blank\">Votex - M12 X 1.25MM Stainless Steel Magnetic Oil Drain Plug with Neodymium Magnet - Made In USA...                    <\/a>\n                <\/td>\n                                    <td class=\"aawp-table__td-rating\" data-label=\"Rating\">\n                                                    <span class=\"aawp-product__rating\"><a class=\"aawp-star-rating aawp-star-rating--large aawp-star-rating--v2\" href=\"https:\/\/www.amazon.com\/dp\/B07YVKL6DQ?tag=700r4hq-20&linkCode=ogi&th=1&psc=1&keywords=magnetic%20oil%20drain%20plug\" title=\"Reviews on Amazon\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"width: 90%;\"><\/span><\/a><\/span>\n                                                                            <span class=\"aawp-product__reviews\">457 Reviews<\/span>\n                                            <\/td>\n                                                <td class=\"aawp-table__td-links\" data-label=\"Link\">\n                    <a class=\"aawp-button aawp-button--buy aawp-button aawp-button--green rounded shadow aawp-button--icon aawp-button--icon-amazon-white\" href=\"https:\/\/www.amazon.com\/dp\/B07YVKL6DQ?tag=700r4hq-20&#038;linkCode=ogi&#038;th=1&#038;psc=1&#038;keywords=magnetic%20oil%20drain%20plug\" title=\"See Current Price\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\">See Current Price<\/a>                <\/td>\n            <\/tr>\n\n                <\/tbody>\n    <\/table>\n\n<\/div>\n\n<p>The oil that\u2019s used in your vehicle will work at its best if it\u2019s uncontaminated. During regular operation, an engine may make a few metal shavings here or there. &nbsp;A magnetic drain plug can grab them and keep them from circulating through the engine.<\/p>\n<p>These particles are often so small that they can\u2019t be seen by the naked eye, but they build up over time and contaminate your oil. The metal particles are measured in microns and are tiny particles. Your car will already have an oil filter that catches the largest particles. The problem is that filters are unable to remove the smallest particles.<\/p>\n<p>Even if you regularly change your car&#8217;s oil, there are still likely to be tiny metal particles contaminating the engine. Over time, these tiny particles can cause wear and tear to your engine. They will be circulated millions of times and will wear down your engine&#8217;s metal components.<\/p>\n<p>Contamination can degrade your engine&#8217;s performance and also shorten its lifespan. Eventually, the engine will wear out completely. The good news is there\u2019s something you can do about this problem. Investing in a magnetic drain plug will help. This small component will remove the most minuscule particles of metal.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2>Pro\u2019s and cons of a magnetic oil drain plug<\/h2>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-180446 alignnone\" src=\"https:\/\/mlabs.info\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Oil-Draining.jpg\" alt=\"Magnetic Oil Plug Pros and Cons\" width=\"500\" height=\"375\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mlabs.info\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Oil-Draining.jpg 500w, https:\/\/mlabs.info\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Oil-Draining-300x225.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Magnetic oil drum plugs are very useful and can be used in cars and other vehicles to prolong the engine&#8217;s life. Let\u2019s look at the pros and cons of using a magnetic oil drain plug.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3>Pro\u2019s<\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li>A magnet is used to collect tiny particles that haven\u2019t been filtered out of the engine. The magnetic drain plug is a small component that looks like a screw. It can be fitted to the engine to remove particles of metal from the oil.<\/li>\n<li>Extends the life of your engine<\/li>\n<li>Your cars will be less likely to experience oil oxidation. This is because the metal shavings that cause oxidation will stick to the magnet and can be removed.<\/li>\n<li>It can also be used to check that your engine is running normally and isn\u2019t producing too many metal shavings.<\/li>\n<li>Cheap and will pay for itself over time. It costs less than purchasing a new OEM drain plug every time you change your oil.<\/li>\n<li>There are many trusted brands available.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h3>Con\u2019s<\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li>There are many cheap, poorly made magnetic drain plugs available that can damage your engine. In some cases, the magnetic block may fall off.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2>Conclusion: &nbsp;Magnetic Oil Drain Plugs are a Good Idea<\/h2>\n<p>As you can see, there are many benefits to buying a magnetic drain plug. They can help to clean the engine&#8217;s oil and remove tiny particles of metal that will be missed by the filter. If you do decide to buy a magnetic drain plug, ensure you choose a trusted brand that creates a good quality product. Be wary of cheap magnetic drain plugs, as these may cause issues with your engine.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Your car&#8217;s oil will work best if it remains uncontaminated. Metal shavings are the worst type of contaminant there is. &nbsp;Magnetic oil drain plugs can catch metal shavings and keep them from doing damage to your car or truck. If you\u2019re wondering whether to invest in a metal oil drain plug, read on. This article &#8230; <a title=\"Magnetic Oil Drain Plugs:  What They Do + Do You Need One?\" class=\"read-more\" href=\"https:\/\/mlabs.info\/magnetic-oil-drain-plugs-what-they-do-do-you-need-one\/\" aria-label=\"More on Magnetic Oil Drain Plugs:  What They Do + Do You Need One?\">Read more<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[3],"tags":[],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/mlabs.info\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/180444"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/mlabs.info\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/mlabs.info\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/mlabs.info\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/mlabs.info\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=180444"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/mlabs.info\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/180444\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/mlabs.info\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=180444"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/mlabs.info\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=180444"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/mlabs.info\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=180444"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}